data.text:
The Melvilles* - Legendary Grape (CD, Album, Ori)

Label: DIG MUSIC

Catalog Number: DIG MUSIC 108

Item Characteristics: CD, Album

Comments: Spine of tray inlay is discolored.

The original album was issued in 1989 as a five hundred copy, cassette-only release on Herman Records. The album was at the time credited to The Melvilles, being one of the names used by Moby Grape during the course of their protracted dispute with former manager Matthew Katz over ownership of the band name and related royalties. The tapes were remastered by Dig Music, and eight additional songs were added for the release of Legendary Grape.

Media Condition: Very Good Plus (VG+)

Sleeve Condition: Very Good Plus (VG+)

_____________________________________

The images shown in this listing were pulled elsewhere from the internet for display purposes only and may not accurately reflect the actual conditions of this item. Please carefully review the Media Condition and Sleeve Condition described above.

If you have any questions or would like to see pictures of the actual item for this listing, please use the Contact page.
